+# Hardening Implementation Report — 2026-06-19
+
+## Scope completed
+
+This patch focuses on the highest-risk stabilization items identified in the architecture review:
+
+1. External provider calls must not hang API/worker capacity indefinitely.
+2. AI-generated JSON must be validated before persistence or workflow branching.
+3. High-use AI HTTP endpoints need consistent schema-based request validation.
+4. Safety checks need regression tests.
+
+## Code changes
+
+### External provider resilience
+
+Added `packages/backend-core/src/lib/externalHttp.ts`, a dependency-free fetch wrapper that provides:
+
+- request timeout via `AbortController`
+- bounded retries with exponential backoff
+- retry handling for `408`, `409`, `425`, `429`, and `5xx`
+- typed `ExternalHttpTimeoutError`
+
+Provider calls now use the wrapper in:
+
+- `apps/api/src/services/apollo.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/services/hunter.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/lib/prospectSources.ts`
+
+Environment knobs added by convention:
+
+- `EXTERNAL_HTTP_TIMEOUT_MS`
+- `EXTERNAL_HTTP_RETRIES`
+- `APOLLO_TIMEOUT_MS`
+- `APOLLO_RETRIES`
+- `HUNTER_TIMEOUT_MS`
+- `HUNTER_RETRIES`
+- `GOOGLE_PLACES_TIMEOUT_MS`
+- `GOOGLE_PLACES_RETRIES`
+
+### Strict AI JSON validation
+
+Added Zod result schemas and parser helpers in `packages/backend-core/src/services/openai.ts`:
+
+- `leadResearchResultSchema`
+- `outreachResultSchema`
+- `replyAnalysisResultSchema`
+- `parseLeadResearchJson`
+- `parseOutreachJson`
+- `parseReplyAnalysisJson`
+
+The parsers throw `ApiError(502, ...)` when model output is invalid, partial, extra-shaped, or semantically unsafe. This fails closed and lets BullMQ retry jobs instead of silently writing nulls or moving leads to the wrong workflow stage.
+
+Validated AI parsing is now used by:
+
+- `apps/worker/src/worker.ts`
+- `apps/worker/src/processors.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/prospects.ts`
+- `scripts/eval-outreach.ts`
+
+### Targeted API request validation
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/ai.ts` now uses Zod schemas for:
+
+- `POST /api/ai/research`
+- `POST /api/ai/outreach`
+- `POST /api/ai/reply-analysis`
+
+The schemas centralize trimming, required fields, max lengths, and error reporting.
+
+### Regression tests added
+
+Added tests:
+
+- `tests/ai-json-validation.test.ts`
+- `tests/external-http.test.ts`
+
+These cover strict AI result parsing, retry behavior, and timeout errors.
+
+## Validation performed
+
+Passed:
+
+```bash
+npm run check:boundaries
+```
+
+Result:
+
+```text
+✓ Boundary check passed — worker does not import apps/api.
+```
+
+Attempted:
+
+```bash
+npm run typecheck
+```
+
+Blocked by missing installed dependencies in the uploaded archive:
+
+```text
+error TS2688: Cannot find type definition file for 'node'.
+```
+
+This is expected because the archive did not include `node_modules`. Run this after `npm ci`:
+
+```bash
+npm run typecheck
+npm test
+npm run test:db
+npm run test:redis
+npm run build
+```
+
+## Remaining recommended work
+
+1. Expand schema validation across the remaining mutation routes, especially:
+   - lead import/create/update
+   - prospect import/update/outcome
+   - mailbox config update
+   - billing checkout/portal actions
+
+2. Add provider-level metrics:
+   - provider request counts
+   - timeout counts
+   - retry counts
+   - circuit-open counts
+
+3. Add idempotency keys for Stripe checkout creation and any future provider mutations.
+
+4. Add a production smoke test that exercises:
+   - `/api/live`
+   - `/api/ready`
+   - `/metrics`
+   - job enqueue/poll lifecycle
+   - one mocked AI parse path
